==English==

===Etymology 1===
possibly from [[triumph]]

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌmp|-ʌmp]]

====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{italbrac|in plural}} The [[suit]], in a [[game]] of [[cards]], that [[outrank]]s all others.
#:''Diamonds were declared '''trumps'''.''
# A [[playing card]] of that suit.
#:''He played an even higher '''trump'''.''
# {{figurative}} Something that gives one an [[advantage]], especially one held in [[reserve]].

{{rft|First def is listed as "in plural" but I've always heard the exact opposite}}

